The '''Omega Butler Refinery''' is a proposed [[oil refinery]] to be built on 121-acres of land in [[Rivers State, Nigeria]]. It will have a capacity of 20,000 barrels per day, along with 90% yield of [[Light crude oil|light oil products]]. Once established, the refinery will reduce fuel cost, create up to 1500 jobs, and contribute to the state's economic growth.
Operational licenses have since been granted by the [[Department of Petroleum Resources]] (DPR) to facilitate the commencement and execution of the project.<ref>{{cite news|title=Rivers State Government Gets License For Omega Butler Refinery|url=http://www.riversstate.gov.ng/item/1441-rivers-state-government-gets-license-for-omega-butler-refinery.html|accessdate=28 May 2015|work=Government of Rivers State|date=5 August 2013}}</ref> On 27 May 2015, it was announced that [[Nigerian naira|₦]]96 billion ([[US$]] 480 million) has been budgeted for engineering procurement, construction, supervision and project management services.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Duke|first1=Russel|title=New Refinery Plus 1,500 New Jobs Coming to Rivers State and Nigeria|url=http://www.ngrguardiannews.com/2015/05/new-refinery-plus-1500-new-jobs-coming-to-rivers-state-and-nigeria/|accessdate=28 May 2015|work=The Guardian|date=27 May 2015}}</ref>
