'''Parasitic mass''' is a [[rocket]], [[weapon]]s and Personal Rapid Transit (PRT or PodCars) transportation term used to differentiate between the [[mass]] of the payload and the moving mass of all other components of the system. It is the mass to which force must be applied to accelerate that is not payload.

A typical [[engineering]] objective is to drive the parasitic mass towards zero. Efficiency gains are achieved as the parasitic mass is reduced.

