{{notability|Companies|date=November 2018}} '''Selling Energy''' is an [[Energy conservation|energy efficiency]] [[consulting firm]] headed by [[Mark Jewell]] and [[Rachel Christenson]]. The firm offers education, training, coaching and financial analysis concerning sales in energy efficiency.<ref>{{cite web|title=EEFG, Inc.|url=https://www.greenedu.com/eefg-inc|website=Green Education Services}}</ref>
Founded in 1993, Selling Energy has provided services for a broad range of customers from individuals to Fortune 500 Companies. Notable clients have included [[Honeywell]], [[PG&E]], [https://hawaiienergy.com/ Hawaii Energy] and [[Belimo]], providing benchmarking, [https://www.forbes.com/sites/ccap/2015/01/19/nano-degrees-as-a-new-model-to-model-to-integrate-into-higher-education/ nano-degrees] and [[continuing education]] concerning efficiency projects.<ref>{{cite web|title=Energy Efficiency Funding Group, Inc.|url=https://credibility.com/engineering-services/us-ca-san-francisco/energy-efficiency-funding-group-inc|website=Credibility.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Stromquist|first1=Eric|title=Day One Honeywell EEO Training: A Word with Mark Jewell|url=http://controltrends.org/2013/08/mark-jewell-on-day-one-of-honeywell-eeo-training/|website=ControlTrends|accessdate=22 August 2014|ref=1}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=PG&E Energy Efficiency Classes - Class Details & Registration|url=http://www.pge.com/mybusiness/edusafety/training/pec/classes/indexClassic.jsp?reqType=detail&ID=6583&db=PEC6583.csv&pageTitle=Class%20Details%20and%20Registration&postback=yes|website=PG&E}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Efficiency Sales Professional Certificate Boot Camp Sponsored by Hawaii Energy|url=http://www.cvent.com/events/the-efficiency-sales-professional-certificate-boot-camp-sponsored-by-hawaii-energy/custom-17-c440f662f7fb4a849ca54b5ebc439b50.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Learning to Sell Efficiency Effectively|url=http://blog.belimo.com/Blog/bid/74449/Learning-to-Sell-Efficiency-Effectively|website=Belimo}}</ref>
